From: kenny@festival.ed.ac.uk (K J MacDonald)
Subject: Re: Benchmarks...?
Date: Sat, 23 Oct 1993 20:51:25 GMT

PAPCC@CUNYVM.CUNY.EDU wrote:

: Hello,

: I would like to perform some benchmarks on my system (486DX2/66) running
: Linux (.99pl13) to see how it compares to the RISC workstations.
: I wonder if someone could point me where to find the program (programs?)
: to do the following tests:

: 1. DHRYSTONES  (for integers num.)
: 2. WHEATSTONES (for floating num.)
: 3. XSTONES     (for graphics)

: or something similar but comprehensive.

From the Linux Software Map (LSM):
Title:       benchmark   Version: 3.11
Desc1:       Byte Magazine Unix Benchmark program
Desc2:       Reports Arithmetic, Filesystem, System calls, Shells
performance
Desc3:       Also includes reports from other platforms (HP, SUN)
Author:      jon@robots.ox.ac.uk (jon@robots.ox.ac.uk)
Maintainer:  jon@robots.ox.ac.uk (jon@robots.ox.ac.uk)
Site1:       tsx-11.mit.edu:/pub/linux/sources/test
suites/benchmark.tar.Z (413153)
Required1:   Linux requires working time, awk and sort (included)
Required2:   Sun, HP
CopyPolicy1: Freely Distributable
Keywords:    benchmark unix performance
Comment1:    Author Ben Smith (ben@bytepb.byte.com)
Comment2:    Binaries were compiled using gcc1.4

        Hope this helps, 

        Kenny.

